$_['help_cache_engine'] = 'Buslik by default.<br />APC is an opcode cache and data store using RAM, suitable for those who do not have the OPCache php extension;<br />APCu is a new version APC is designed to store data using RAM only. It is recommended to enable OpCache on the server;<br />Buslik is the same as a file cache, but allows you to store cache files divided into folders depending on the route, etc., thereby speeding up the search for the desired cache file and allowing you to store a larger number ;<br />Memcache - caching data in RAM based on a hash table;<br />Memcached - a new version of Memcache for caching data in RAM based on a hash table;<br />OpCache - the same as Buslik, but saves the cache as PHP code. Requires 2 times more disk space. First, the PHP code is created, then the second pass is saved using the php extension algorithm OpCache;<br />Redis is the same as Memcached;<br />WinCache is a caching module that allows you to increase the speed of PHP applications on Windows and Windows Server . The handler includes its algorithm for working with data using RAM and disk memory;<br />xCache - includes its algorithm for working with data using RAM and disk memory.';
