$_['doc'] = '<b>Understand all quoted values without spaces inside (example: \' | \' hence => \'|\'). Also, do not leave empty lines in the settings so that the module does not fulfill unnecessary check conditions. All settings are given in a single writing style, but be careful and look at the instructions when hovering over a circle with a question mark.</b><br /><br /><b>Route</b> is the value of the GET parameter in the address line of the browser after the character \' = \' (example: route=product/category => product/category), or when loading the controller in the code, the first parameter (example: $this->load->controller(\'product/category\') => product/category), or when loading a model (example: $this->model_catalog_category->getCategories() => catalog/category/getCategories). In OpenCart 4 controller function is already preceded by \' | \' or \' . \', but you still put \' / \'.<br />The route and keyword of the page can be found when you turn on the debug mode at the very top. <b>The route can also be another parameter from the query column of the oc_url_alias, oc_seo_url table (when there is no route in the browser line, but there is a keyword instead of the product/category route, for example, path = 20_27) - this behavior is planned to be changed in the future (the ability to specify routes separated by commas, for example, for caching categories product/category,path=,category_id=)</b>.<br /><br />
I recommend using this <a href="https://liveopencart.ru/index.php?route=product/product&product_id=2519" rel="noreferrer noopener">module</a> and specify the link there:<br />< br />
