Clear GUEST CART SESSION (guest cart session data): <br /><br />';
$_['doc_status'] = '<b>Status</b> is the status of the module or its functionality.<br />Enabled - all module functions will be operational.<br />Disabled - all module functions will be inoperative. <br />Between status changes and saving settings, the OpenCart cache in system/storage/cache will be cleared, modifiers and (or) events will be updated.<br />Modifiers and (or) module events will be enabled and disabled depending on the status.' ;
$_['doc_store'] = '<b>Shop</b> is the status of the module or its functionality on the pages of the selected store.<br />The list of stores is located in the Admin panel/System/Settings. Enabling work is determined by checking the checkbox.';
$_['doc_cache_status'] = '<b>Enable page caching</b> - this is the operating status of the module functionality related to entire page caching.<br />Yes - page cache functions will be functional.<br />No - functions page cache will not work.<br />Functions related to this setting will disappear when disabled.<br />It is not recommended to cache the site if you have HDD storage memory rather than SSD (NVMe). In general, do not rent hosting or a server unless it has NVMe installed.';
$_['doc_cache_con'] = '<b>config parameters</b> are string or array parameters retrieved from $this->config->get(). The variety of the cache by these parameters will be valid for the cache of all pages, controllers, models. You have to manually open source and look for $this->config->get() which can be different under certain conditions (i.e. you need to create a new cache when $this->config->get() changes).';
$_['doc_cache_ses'] = '<b>session parameters</b> are array parameters obtained from $this->session->data. Cache diversity by these parameters will be valid for the cache of all pages, except for the cache of controllers, models. You have to manually open the source code and look for $this->session->data which can be different under certain conditions (i.e. you need to create a new cache when $this->session->data changes).';
$_['doc_cache_cok'] = '<b>Cookie parameters</b> are array parameters obtained from $this->request->cookie. Cache diversity by these parameters will be valid for the cache of all pages, except for the cache of controllers, models. You have to manually open source and look for $this->request->cookie which can be different under certain conditions (i.e. you need to create a new cache when $this->request->cookie changes).';
$_['doc_cache_par'] = '<b>Restriction parameters</b> are array parameters obtained from $this->request->get and $this->request->post. The cache limit on these parameters will be valid for the cache of all pages, except for the cache of controllers, models. You manually need to open the source code and look for $this->request->get ($_GET) and $this->request->post ($_POST) which can be different under certain conditions (that is, you need to create a new cache when $this changes ->request->get and $this->request->post).';
$_['doc_cache_onrot'] = '<b>Operation parameters</b> - this function is responsible for caching entire pages for a narrow setting (the ability to configure the cache for individual pages by route and keyword, specify individual settings: cache time, config parameters , session, cookie, get and post for cache diversity).';
