$_['doc_cache_controller'] = '<b>Caching controller functions</b> - this function is responsible for caching controllers loaded in the code via $this->load->controller();. For each controller, you can specify individual settings: cache time, config parameters (takes from the general settings by default), session, cookie, get and post for cache variety.';
$_['doc_cache_controller_ajax'] = '<b>Ajax loading controller functions</b> - this function is responsible for loading ajax controllers in the way loaded in the code via $this->load->controller();. This function should be used if you need to hide information from search robots, when a module has a lot of the same words on the page, or when the module cannot be cached when caching the entire page.';
